Reasoning: The paper analyzes data collected from smartphones to investigate the interplay between different activity types, namely communication, motion, and physical proximity. This involves the use of social network analysis, statistical modeling, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
